<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="19" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d19">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4062/11–12.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Francis</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-07-16"><hi rend="italic">July 16,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The department has received your No. 225
                            of the 8th of May last, relative to the expulsion case of Mr. Selig
                            Fink, and awaits the reply of the foreign office to your note of May 7
                            last on this case and on the general question involved of former
                            Austrian or Hungarian subjects returning as American citizens to the
                            country of their origin.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>